# Startup Flow

## Status: Implemented

## Overview

The app uses a phase-gated startup flow managed by a Pinia state machine (`startupStore`).
On first launch, a 3-step setup wizard runs. On subsequent launches, the app either auto-loads
the last character or presents a character picker.

## Startup Phases

```
First launch:
  splash ‚Üí setup-path ‚Üí setup-watchers ‚Üí setup-character ‚Üí loading ‚Üí ready

Returning user (auto-load enabled):
  splash ‚Üí loading ‚Üí ready

Returning user (auto-load disabled):
  splash ‚Üí select-character ‚Üí loading ‚Üí ready
```

Phase transitions are controlled by `startupStore.goToPhase()` and driven by
`startupStore.initialize()` which reads settings to determine the starting phase.

## First-Time Setup Wizard

### Step 1: Game Folder (`SetupPathStep.vue`)
- Auto-detects `%AppData%\..\LocalLow\Elder Game\Project Gorgon\` on Windows
- User can browse or type a path
- Backend validates the path via `validate_game_data_path` and returns booleans for:
  - Folder exists
  - Player.log found
  - ChatLogs/ found
  - Reports/ found
- Green checkmarks shown for each found item
- "Next" requires the folder to exist

### Step 2: Watchers (`SetupWatchersStep.vue`)
- Toggle: auto-watch Player.log on startup (default on)
- Toggle: auto-watch Chat logs on startup (default on)
- Saves to `autoTailPlayerLog` and `autoTailChat` settings

### Step 3: Character (`SetupCharacterStep.vue`)
- If Reports/ was found in step 1, scans for `Character_*.json` files via
  `scan_reports_for_characters` and shows discovered characters as selectable buttons
- Manual entry: character name + server dropdown (servers from `get_server_list`)
- Toggle: auto-load last character on startup (default on)
- "Finish Setup" saves the character to `user_characters`, sets it active, and
  calls `complete_setup` which sets `setup_completed = true`

## Returning User Flow

### Auto-load (`autoLoadLastCharacter = true`)
Settings already have `activeCharacterName` and `activeServerName` from last session.
`initialize()` skips straight to the `loading` phase, runs startup tasks, then enters `ready`.

### Character selection (`autoLoadLastCharacter = false`)
`initialize()` loads all `user_characters` from the database and shows `CharacterSelect.vue`.
Users pick from known characters or add a new one manually.

## Settings Fields (settings.rs / settingsStore.ts)

| Field | Type | Default | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|---------|
| `setup_completed` | bool | false | Gates first-time wizard vs normal launch |
| `active_character_name` | Option<String> | None | Last-used character name |
| `active_server_name` | Option<String> | None | Last-used server name |
| `auto_load_last_character` | bool | true | Skip character picker on launch |

## Database: user_characters Table (migration_v2)

```sql
CREATE TABLE user_characters (
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    character_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    server_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    source TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source IN ('report', 'manual', 'login')),
    is_active BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    latest_report_time TIMESTAMP,
    last_login_time TIMESTAMP,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    UNIQUE(character_name, server_name)
);
```

The `UNIQUE(character_name, server_name)` constraint handles deduplication across sources.
If a user manually enters "Zenith/Dreva" and later a report or login is detected for the
same pair, the row is updated via `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` rather than creating a duplicate.

### Sources
- `report` ‚Äî discovered from a `Character_*.json` file in the Reports folder
- `manual` ‚Äî entered by the user during setup or character selection
- `login` ‚Äî detected from Player.log via the coordinator's CharacterLogin event

## Backend Commands (setup_commands.rs)

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `validate_game_data_path(path)` | Returns which expected files/folders exist at the path |
| `scan_reports_for_characters(path)` | Parses Character_*.json files, returns deduplicated character list |
| `save_user_character(name, server, source)` | Upserts into user_characters |
| `get_user_characters()` | Returns all characters ordered by active first, then most recent |
| `set_active_character(name, server)` | Sets one character active, clears others, updates settings |
| `complete_setup()` | Sets `setup_completed = true` in settings |
| `get_server_list()` | Returns hardcoded PG server names (Dreva, Arisetsu, Laeth, Miraverre, Strekios) |

## Auto-Registration on Login (coordinator.rs)

When the `PlayerLogWatcher` detects a `CharacterLogin` event, the coordinator:
1. Upserts the character into `user_characters` with `source='login'`
2. Updates `active_character_name` in settings

This means characters are automatically discovered as the user plays, without
requiring manual entry or report imports.

## Active Character Display (MenuBar.vue)

The MenuBar shows the active character name and server on the right side next to the
settings gear. Character name uses `text-text-primary`, server uses `text-text-muted`.

